text: Karen Seel is the District 5 Commissioner in Pinellas County, Florida. Seel was appointed to the board in 1999 by Governor Jeb Bush to fill an unexpired term. She was first elected in 2000 to a four-year term and again in 2004. Seel attended the University of Florida for her bachelor's degree.
